The paper focuses on a novel approach and database for 3D object modeling, printing, and tracking for robotic manipulation research. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as well as computer vision (cs.CV) since the approach involves using monocular or RGB-D camera images to generate 3D models. The paper also mentions the use of texture mapping, which falls under computer graphics (cs.GR). Additionally, the approach involves tracking objects, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) depending on the specific tracking algorithm used.
